Node.Notes: Uncertain, with "inscription/inscriptional psalm best guess. Other suggestions include atonement psalm/golden psalm.
Text is second feminine singular "you said," most change vowel to get first singular "I said."
Difficult text, which seems to say "my good is not upon you." Some suggest "not" functions as affirmative "indeed." Most reinterpret as something like "my good is not apart from you."
Uncertain. Seems to be "As for all the holy ones which are in the land and the glorious ones, all of my delight is in them."
Some change vowels to get "my glorious/mighty ones," and so avoid difficulty of a construct noun left hanging by itself.
Some details in the verse uncertain. General sense is that the psalmist declares that he will not participate in idol worship.
Uncertain. Could be go/do something quickly or acquire something by paying for it.
Probably offerings of the blood of sacrificed animals.
Probably "not take up their names upon my lips" means "not invoke these idols in worship"
Some think "glory" is a way of speaking about an individual, given parallel with "heart" and "flesh" here, and also evidence of ps7:5.
